'''Google Inc.''' ({{nasdaq|GOOG}} and {{lse|GGEA}}) is an [[United States|American]] [[Multinational corporation|multinational]] [[software]] [[corporation]], first [[Incorporation|incorporated]] as a [[Private company|privately held corporation]] in September, 1998, that specializes in search engine, information retrieval technology and online advertising. With a market capitalization of [[United States dollar|US$]]118.32 billion as of June [[2006]], Google is the largest internet search company in the world, almost twice as large as rival [[Yahoo!]]<ref>Khan, Kim; Blaine, Charley. "[http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/CNBCTV/Articles/Dispatches/P136522.asp Google stock tops $400, worth $117.6 billion]." ''[[MSN|MSN Money]].'' [[June 9]], [[2006]].</ref> The company employs approximately 6,800 employees and is based in [[Mountain View, California]]<ref>"[http://www.google.com/press/pressrel/revenues_q106.html Google Announces First Quarter 2006 Results]." (Press Release) ''[[Google]].'' [[April 20]], [[2006]]. Retrieved on [[July 6]], [[2006]].</ref> ({{coor dms|37|25|19|N|122|5|3|W|type:company_scale:1000}}). [[Eric E. Schmidt|Eric Schmidt]], formerly [[chief executive officer]] of [[Novell]], was named Google's CEO when co-founder [[Lawrence E. Page|Larry Page]] stepped down.
The name "Google" originated from a common misspelling of "[[googol]],"<ref>Koller, David. "[http://graphics.stanford.edu/~dk/google_name_origin.html Origin of the name, "Google."] ''[[Stanford University]].'' January, [[2004]].</ref> which refers to 10<sup>100</sup> (a 1 followed by one-hundred zeros). Google has since become well known for its corporate culture and innovative products and has a major impact on online culture.
